aiiwav.\ngive the reaper the assurance, even if\nif is only superficial, of the improv\ned conditions of the company.\nFreight fcr Hawaii.\nSEATTLE, August 3. In order to\ndivert to Seattle from San Francisco\nfreight destined for the Hawaiian Isl\nands, the Chicago Milwaukee Puget\nSound Railway has just put into effect\nnew tariffs v.nler which such freight\nwill be deliver-d at tdiipside on Puget\nSound at the same rate as at San.\nFrancisco.\nHeretofore the southern lines have\nassumed the cost of shipside delivery,\nwhile northern toads have not done so.\nHereafter the Milwaukee will assume\nthe cost of shirsile delivery, thus\nvill be completed about the placing Pugi-t Sound pcrts on an equal-\nV d if xt year and piacea in inei,ty with California competitors\nIjrJiln-San irancisco senicc\nii nil Arrived, Auir. 'J sehr. Seuuoia\nfiom Cray's Harbor.\nSeattle Sailed, Aug. 1M. S. S. Hy\nades for Honolulu.\nCaviota Arrived. Aug. 24. S. S.\nRoseirans. from Kaanapali. Aug. M.\nHilo Sailed, Aug. 24. S. S. Hilonian\nfor San Francisco.\nsteamers\n11 frnm\n.MQTI\nTbeMifMurian is due to arrive to-\niv -jcr.can-iia\nMl eood ileal more general prod-\ntof tie Man1s tban last Sf':,so'3\n;fjorsf said his comyany had han\nt J Quantities of wool, honey,\n.japplMand other products exclusive\ns agar-\nGeorgian and Honolulan.\nfreighter Georgian of the\nji-Hawaiian line was given a\n4 5ip recently, and she made four\ni teot3 an hour. The Georgian is\nlseet long, 53 feet and 6 inches\ni'ltd 39 feet deep, built by the\nUud Shipbuilding Company. She\nIf v used in the Atlantic service.\nP i ..a. t, iia\nHonOlUlaB, a slsierMup iu iuc\nr\nNEXT MAILS.\nCoast, Orient and Colonial.\nJ\nMails are due from the following\npoints as follows:\nSau Francisco Per Sierra, today.\nVokohama 1'er Siberia. Mondav.\nAustralia Per Marama, Sept. 13.\nVictoria Per Zealandia, Sept. 16.\nMails will depart for the following\npoints as follows:\n!,San Francisco Per Siberia Aim 5!).\nVokohama For Korea. Monday.